descript.abstract: Pennsylvania Hospitals that are licensed or approved by the PA Dept. of Health and Public Welfare or part of the Facilities Resource Emergency Database (FRED). Licensed or approved hospitals are those identified from the July 1, 2010 to June 30, 2011 reporting period.
descript.purpose: This layer was developed for use by emergency service organizations and the general public.
descript.supplinf: All geocoded points were rectified to building rooftops when possible. The user should assume some spatial inaccuracy.

attr.attrdef: Hospitals with nuclear medicine departments are designated to decontaminate and treat victims in the time of an event at a nuclear power plant. Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) requires at least a primary and secondary hospital to service each nuclear facility. This field contains the name or names of the nuclear facilities that a hospital services in the time of a nuclear event at a power plant.
attr.attrdefs: Pennsylvania Emergency Management Agency (PEMA) is responsible for the designation of these hospitals. PEMA runs drills on the facilities, writes reports on the outcomes, and ensures that the designated hospitals maintain the service level that FEMA requires. Victor Wilson at PEMA currently oversees these drills.

attr.attrdef: Name of minor civil division where hospital is located.
Minor civil division FIPS key code containing state, county, and MCD FIPS string.
